---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms and Conditions • Secura Security Suite">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#050507] text-neutral-200 selection:bg-cyan-500 selection:text-black flex flex-col justify-between">
    <Header />

    <div class="flex-1 relative">
      <!-- Grid Background overlay -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(rgba(6,182,212,0.03)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(6,182,212,0.03)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:32px_32px] opacity-40 pointer-events-none"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-1/3 w-[450px] h-[450px] bg-indigo-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>

      <!-- Content Container -->
      <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 z-10">
        
        <!-- Header back button -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <a 
            href="/" 
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors uppercase tracking-wider group"
          >
            <span class="transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform inline-block">&larr;</span>
            <span>Back to Home</span>
          </a>
        </div>

      <!-- Hero Header -->
      <div class="border-b border-neutral-900 pb-10 mb-12">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-cyan-950/40 border border-cyan-500/30 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan-400 mb-6 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(6,182,212,0.1)]">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span>SECURA COMPLIANCE INFRASTRUCTURE</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-white mb-6 font-mono">
          TERMS & CONDITIONS
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-neutral-500">
          Last Updated: July 17, 2026 &bull; Version 1.9.0 (Stable)
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Terms Content -->
      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed font-sans max-w-3xl">
        
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">1. Scope of Service Accordance</h2>
          <p>
            By instantiating an active user session or creating a registered profile on Secura (referred to as the "Platform" or "Service"), you explicitly agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms and Conditions. These terms govern the secure utilization of our unified workspace environments, including credentials archiving, client-side invoicing, and financial trackers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">2. Sovereign Cryptographic Key Responsibility</h2>
          <p>
            Because Secura is engineered using zero-knowledge client-side encryption, <strong>you bear 100% of the cryptographic responsibility for preserving your Master Vault Password</strong>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-yellow-500 font-mono text-xs">
            WARNING: If you forget or lose your Master Vault Password, we have no theoretical or mechanical bypass to decrypt or recover your credentials, transaction tables, or invoice databases. Backup your keys safely!
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">3. Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
          <p>
            You agree not to utilize the Platform to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 mt-3 text-neutral-350 pl-2">
            <li>Generate fake, misleading, or fraudulent invoices for tax avoidance.</li>
            <li>Store or trade stolen authentication credentials that do not belong to you.</li>
            <li>Launch automated DDoS scripts, credential-stuffing exploits, or brute-force requests targeting Secura’s network endpoints.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">4. Subscription Fees, Refunds & Billing</h2>
          <p>
            We provide a default Free Starter Tier with standard capabilities and limits. Upgrading to our Premium Tier binds you to standard monthly subscription fees billed via secure Stripe handlers. Subscriptions can be canceled at any time directly through your Billing Settings and remain active until the end of the current billing cycle.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">5. Exclusion of Warranty and Liabilities</h2>
          <p>
            Secura provides its suite on an "As-Is" and "As-Available" basis without express or implied warranty of any kind. Since all cryptographic keys are operated locally, Secura shall not be held liable for local data loss, hardware corruption, master key compromise, or operational business interruptions.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Footer stamp -->
      <div class="border-t border-neutral-900 mt-16 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-neutral-600">SECURA LEGAL COMPLIANCE TEAM &bull; NORTH AMERICA SECTION</span>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-neutral-500">MEMBER REGISTRY #891-SEC</span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</div>
</Layout>
